description:
Detailed information concerning twenty of Zero Month's main #0 titles, including select members of the Justice League, Green Lantern and even Starman. A must see for any Zero Month collector or enthusiast.

Notes:

  • Cover title is Zero Month but indica has Zero Hour Sampler 1994.
  • Sampler design by Murphy Fogelnest.
name: The Beginning of Tomorrow

description: A sneak peak preview into what the events of Zero Hour #0 will entail.  The illustrations without color suggest this to be a director's cut of certain events pertaining to Zero Hour's conclusion.
name: Eyes Only/Top Secret

description: A post-Zero Hour  edition outlining the issues of Zero Month and what that event will entail for the DCU.
name: The Beginning of Tomorrow

description:
Special adventure of the Moth intended to be a prelude to a larger Moth 4-issue miniseries.

In addition to this original story there are selections of Steve Rude's artwork on the Moth and other characters.
name: Special Edition

volume.name: Free Comic Book Day: The Moth

description:
Run! Hide! Call the authorities! You’ll find all your efforts futile...It was foolish to think you could escape Creepy #6! There will be no mercy shown as you recoil in horror at tales brought to you by Joe R. Lansdale, Nathan Fox, Christopher A. Taylor, Jason Shawn Alexander, Alice Henderson, and more! Featuring 48 bone-chilling pages Creepy #6 will make your summer scream!

Story Titles

  • Mine
  • Commedia Dell' Morte!
  • The Wreck
  • Loathsome Lore
  • Fair Exchange
name: Mine; Commedia Dell Morte; The Wreck; Loathsome Lore; Fair Exchange;

description: HOUSE M.D. MEETS FRINGE IN THE FIRST SKYBOUND ORIGINAL FROM ROBERT KIRKMAN's NEW COMICS IMPRINT! Meet Vincent Morrow, a doctor looking for a vaccine... for the apocalypse! In this stand-alone first issue, a family needs Dr. Morrow's help with their son's illness: Demonic possession. But when Morrow attempts an experimental cure, he discovers the boy's disease isn't all spinning heads and pea soup - it's like nothing you've seen before! Horror gets a brain transplant in WITCH DOCTOR, the book WARREN ELLIS calls 'Mental.'

The Red Scorpion gang has terrorized the countryside for months, and its members have been the culprits behind many of Usagi’s recent adventures. In this issue, Usagi finally faces the Red Scorpion himself! But defeating both the Scorpion and the mercenaries at his side may be too much even for the rabbit ronin.
name: Those Who Tread on the Scorpion's Tail, Part Three

description: Inspector Thomas Adye of Scotland Yard arrested the wrong man when he locked Leather Apron up for the murders of several White chapel prostitutes. Jack the Ripper is still on the loose and, worse, appears to be in league with powerful forces that have a vested interest in keeping him in business. Adye once again turns to the imprisoned Dr. Henry Jekyll for help. Will their unholy alliance redeem our hero from his arrogant mistakes, or push him even closer to the edge of the abyss Jekyll calls home?
name: 3 (of 4)

volume.name: The Strange Case of Mr. Hyde

description: What would you do if you hit rock bottom and there was no way out? If you had tried to take the final escape and discovered that path was blocked? In the case of Alec King, the suicidal immortal, you pick up a gun and set out to take out the bastards responsible for your misery. A class noir revenge tale with a supernatural twist from Minotaur Press!
name: Regicide Part Two
